other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen Without and With Contrast
other_tests.findings: Severe hepatic steatosis with a vague region of hypoattenuating triangular parenchyma in segment III suggestive of focal fatty deposition. Very mild edema and peripancreatic stranding around the pancreatic neck, head, and uncinate process. No significant pancreatic ductal dilatation or vascular complication. No pseudocysts. No significant free fluid in the retroperitoneum. Remaining intra-abdominal organs appear unremarkable.
